<br>1. What is the motivation for the company to take on this project?
<br>2. Clearly articulate how the proposed technology will result in a soci=
etal benefit. Which communities will benefit and on what timeline?
<br>3. How will the societal benefits be measured and tracked?
<br>4. What steps are being taken to recognize and minimize the unintended =
consequences of the proposed technology?
<br>
<br>Commercial:
<br>1. What is the background of the team, why is this the right team to ex=
ecute the commercialization of the proposed innovation?
<br>2. What is the size and scope of the market opportunity? You must ident=
ify how you plan to make a scalable, sustainable business from this effort.
<br>3. Who is the customer for the innovation? What is the value propositio=
n for your customer?
<br>4. What does the competitive landscape look like? What is your competit=
ive advantage? (Please search NSF awards database for prior similar technol=
ogy awards)
<br>5. Which group of customers want the product/technology being proposed?
<br>6. What customer(s) needs or requirements will be satisfied by the prop=
osed product? Is this a need to have or a nice to have?
<br>7. How are the needs and requirement(s) being satisfied now?
<br>8. Why will the customer choose the proposed product over existing solu=
tions?
<br>
